                    <p>Over 4 million books are published every year — more than 11,000 per day. Without a strategic visibility plan, your book becomes one of millions — undiscovered and unread. This isn't a reflection of your talent. It's the reality of today's publishing landscape.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="problem-card fade-in">
                    <div class="problem-icon">📱</div>
                    <h3>The Social Media Trap</h3>
                    <p>You post every day. You share quotes. You ask people to buy. And nothing happens. Most authors use social media without a clear strategy, without understanding their audience, and without a conversion path. Social media can be powerful — but only when used strategically.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="problem-card fade-in">
                    <div class="problem-icon">🦗</div>
                    <h3>The Launch Disaster</h3>
                    <p>You spent months writing your book. You hit publish. You share the news. You get a small spike in sales. Then silence. A successful book launch isn't about one big day — it's about a strategic campaign that builds momentum before, during, and after launch.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="problem-card fade-in">
                    <div class="problem-icon">🤯</div>
                    <h3>The DIY Marketing Nightmare</h3>
                    <p>YouTube videos, blog posts, Facebook groups — you've tried to piece together a marketing plan from free advice and you're more confused than ever. One expert says TikTok. Another says email. You're overwhelmed and spending more time on marketing than writing.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="problem-card fade-in">
                    <div class="problem-icon">🪞</div>
                    <h3>The Branding Blind Spot</h3>
                    <p>Most authors think marketing is just about selling books. But successful authors understand it's about building a BRAND. Your author brand is what makes readers choose YOUR book. Without a strong brand, you're just another name on a cover.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="problem-card fade-in">
                    <div class="problem-icon">💰</div>
                    <h3>The Revenue Challenge</h3>
                    <p>Your book isn't generating the income you expected. Sales aren't consistent. What most authors don't realize: the book is often just the starting point. The real opportunities emerge when your book gives you visibility — but that requires strategic marketing.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="problem-card fade-in">
                    <div class="problem-icon">😟</div>
                    <h3>The Confidence Challenge</h3>
                    <p>You know your book is good and your message matters. But watching other authors succeed while you struggle breeds doubt. Your struggle isn't about your worth — it's about the lack of proper marketing strategy. Every visible author has marketing effort behind them.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="problem-card fade-in">
                    <div class="problem-icon">🔍</div>
                    <h3>The Media Mystery</h3>
                    <p>Other authors are getting featured on blogs, publications, and online platforms. Getting media coverage isn't luck — it's strategy. It requires a compelling story, a polished media kit, targeted pitches, and systematic outreach.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="problem-card fade-in">
                    <div class="problem-icon">📧</div>
                    <h3>The Email List Neglect</h3>
                    <p>Your email list is the ONLY audience you truly own. Social media algorithms can change tomorrow. But your email list is yours. It's one of the most powerful tools an author can have — yet most authors either don't have one or don't know how to use it.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="problem-card fade-in">
                    <div class="problem-icon">🗺️</div>
